{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856987407,"sessionID":"ses_286ae3044ffemHzEQmhqlh3J9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7952a6e5001SC8xAa7SkxmUCy","messageID":"msg_d7952985a001fPsq6r4QWxjocG","sessionID":"ses_286ae3044ffemHzEQmhqlh3J9m","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_390b0bfa93c94f208ec4f885","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PicoD JWT middleware in `pkg/picod`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-017\n- **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs. This delta covers the JWT middleware implementation in `pkg/picod`, specifically the AuthManager component that handles RSA public key loading and JWT token validation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-017-001: RSA Public Key Loading\n\n**Description:** The system must support loading an RSA public key from an environment variable for JWT signature verification.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-001-A — Load valid RSA public key from environment variable\n\n**GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with a valid PEM-encoded RSA public key  \n**WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n**THEN** the public key is successfully parsed and stored in the AuthManager  \n**AND** subsequent calls to `GetPublicKey()` return the loaded RSA public key\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-001-B — Missing environment variable\n\n**GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set  \n**WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n**THEN** an error is returned with message `\"environment variable PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY is not set\"`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-001-C — Invalid PEM format\n\n**GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with invalid PEM data  \n**WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n**THEN** an error is returned with message `\"failed to decode PEM block\"`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-001-D — Non-RSA public key\n\n**GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with a valid PEM-encoded EC (elliptic curve) public key  \n**WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n**THEN** an error is returned with message `\"public key is not an RSA key\"`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-001-E — Thread-safe key update\n\n**GIVEN** an AuthManager has already loaded a valid public key  \n**WHEN** multiple goroutines call `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` concurrently to update the key  \n**THEN** no race conditions occur  \n**AND** `GetPublicKey()` always returns a valid public key or nil\n\n---\n\n### AR-017-002: JWT Bearer Token Validation\n\n**Description:** The middleware must validate JWT Bearer tokens from the Authorization header using the loaded RSA public key.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-A — Missing Authorization header\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made to a protected endpoint without an `Authorization` header  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Missing authorization header\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"JWT required: Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-B — Invalid Authorization header format (not Bearer)\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with `Authorization: Basic dXNlcjpwYXNz`  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid authorization header format\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-C — Malformed Bearer token format\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with `Authorization: Bearer` (no token)  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid authorization header format\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-D — Public key not configured\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a valid Bearer token but the AuthManager has no public key loaded (publicKey is nil)  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid token\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Public key not configured\"}`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-E — Valid JWT token with RSA signature\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a valid JWT token signed with the corresponding RSA private key  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is allowed to proceed to the next handler  \n**AND** `c.Next()` is called\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-F — Invalid JWT signature\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token that has an invalid RSA signature  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid token\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"verification failed\"}`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-G — JWT with wrong signing method\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token signed using HS256 (HMAC) instead of RS256 (RSA)  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response body contains detail about the unexpected signing method\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-H — Expired JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token that has expired (exp claim is in the past)  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response indicates the token is invalid due to expiration\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-I — JWT token without expiration claim\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token that has no `exp` (expiration) claim  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n**AND** the response indicates expiration is required\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-002-J — Request body size limit enforcement\n\n**GIVEN** a valid JWT token is provided in the Authorization header  \n**WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n**THEN** the request body is wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting it to 32 MiB  \n**AND** oversized requests will be rejected before reaching handlers\n\n---\n\n### AR-017-003: Public Key Accessor\n\n**Description:** The system must provide thread-safe access to the loaded public key.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-003-A — Get public key after loading\n\n**GIVEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` has successfully loaded a valid RSA public key  \n**WHEN** `GetPublicKey()` is called  \n**THEN** the RSA public key is returned  \n**AND** the operation is thread-safe (read lock)\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-003-B — Get public key when not loaded\n\n**GIVEN** the AuthManager was created with `NewAuthManager()` (no key loaded)  \n**WHEN** `GetPublicKey()` is called  \n**THEN** nil is returned  \n**AND** no error occurs\n\n---\n\n### AR-017-004: RequireAuth Helper\n\n**Description:** The system should provide a convenience middleware that loads the public key on first use and then validates tokens.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-004-A — RequireAuth loads key and validates\n\n**GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with a valid RSA public key  \n**WHEN** `RequireAuth()` middleware is invoked on a request with a valid JWT  \n**THEN** the public key is loaded from environment  \n**AND** the request proceeds through `AuthMiddleware()`\n\n---\n\n#### Scenario: AR-017-004-B — RequireAuth fails if key cannot be loaded\n\n**GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set  \n**WHEN** `RequireAuth()` middleware is invoked  \n**THEN** the server logs a fatal error via `klog.Fatalf`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Data Structures\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | Environment variable for RSA public key |\n| `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | Maximum request body size |\n\n### Key Behaviors\n\n1. **Public Key Loading**: RSA public key loaded from PEM-encoded environment variable\n2. **Token Validation**: JWT Bearer tokens validated using RSA signature\n3. **Thread Safety**: RWMutex protects public key access for concurrent reads\n4. **Validation Rules**:\n   - Signing method must be RSA (RS256, RS384, RS512)\n   - Expiration (`exp`) claim is required\n   - Issued at (`iat`) claim is validated\n   - 1 minute leeway allowed for time tolerance\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Module: `pkg/picod`\n- Auth Implementation: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n- Related: AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API - includes full server integration)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go\">\nERROR [157:44] vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method ZaddScoreMember)\nERROR [157:67] undefined: valkey.ZaddScoreMember\nERROR [158:50] vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method ZaddScoreMember)\nERROR [158:73] undefined: valkey.ZaddScoreMember\nERROR [338:65] vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Score undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method Score)\nERROR [348:9] vs.cli.Close() (no value) used as value\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go\">\nERROR [94:16] undefined: metav1\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go\">\nERROR [15:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch\" imported and not used\nERROR [66:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [81:9] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [95:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [109:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [132:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [160:14] cannot u